attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, with debug_info, not stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a Mirai-based malware variant, specifically a botnet agent designed for Linux-based IoT devices. It features multiple DDoS attack vectors (TCP SYN/ACK/STOMP, UDP, GRE), a competition killer that terminates other botnet processes by scanning /proc/net/tcp, and a specialized scanner module. A prominent feature is the 'huawei_init' function, which targets Huawei Home Gateways via a UPnP SOAP vulnerability (DeviceUpgrade_1) to achieve remote command execution. The exploit payload attempts to download further components from 45.91.116.104 using busybox wget. It uses process name spoofing ('/var/Sofia') and watchdog manipulation to ensure persistence and evade detection.
